messages.content: ComfyUI-FaceSwap is a basic custom node that enables face swapping functionality in ComfyUI.
Does ComfyUI-FaceSwap currently support GPU processing?
No, ComfyUI-FaceSwap only runs on CPU at the moment. GPU support is planned for a future update.
What is the resolution of the model used by ComfyUI-FaceSwap?
The current model used by ComfyUI-FaceSwap is 128x128, which may lead to lower quality results at larger resolutions.
To install ComfyUI-FaceSwap, users need to navigate to the custom_nodes directory in their ComfyUI installation, clone the ComfyUI-FaceSwap repository, and restart ComfyUI.
What inputs are required for the FaceSwapNode?
The FaceSwapNode requires an image of a face or faces and an image to swap the face into. Users can then select the source face and specify which faces to replace using comma-separated indices.
Can multiple faces be replaced in a single scene using ComfyUI-FaceSwap?
Yes, users can chain multiple FaceSwapNodes to replace multiple faces in a single scene.
